                    "comment": "wesm commented on issue #6874: [DO NOT MERGE] ARROW-8368: [C++][C Data Interface] Move several child arrays\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/6874#issuecomment-613130687\n \n \n   This seems acceptable to me, since it accounts for the use case where a consumer wishes to project a subset of fields from a producer where they may not be able to \"push down\" their subset intention into the producer request (comparing `select * from ...` with `select $0, $1, $2, ..., $k`). Should the format docs be amended to state that moving multiple children is permissible so long as the moves and then parent-release are handled as an \"atomic surgery\"? \n \n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on to GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
